thread.title: Medibank, Calvary restart contract talks

title: Medibank, Calvary restart contract talks
text:
Wed, Aug 26, 2015, 6:51 PM AEST - Australia Markets closed Medibank, Calvary restart contract talks AAP â€“ 4 minutes 46 seconds ago Recommend Print 
Health insurer Medibank Private and hospital operator Calvary have resumed formal contract talks. 
In a statement on Wednesday, the warring parties said they restarted negotiations on the contract set to expire on August 31, but would not go into details. 
Calvary CEO Mark Doran and Medibank official Andrew Wilson described the talks as fruitful and said they were both encouraged by the progress of the discussions. @y7finance on Twitter, become a fan on Facebook Terms
